Tom,<br><br>
I really can't think of anyone better to be &quot;stuck&quot; with! An honest man is hard to find. Though some might not totally agree with you sometimes, your honesty and candor is appreciated, at least by me, and I enjoy your way of trying to level the playing field.<br><br>
In the line of Cook's reasoning:<br><br>
One of my more outstanding memories after 'Nam was my roommate in school, a Canadian, telling me that he was asked to room with me by campus housing because no &quot;American&quot; wanted to. They were afraid I would awaken in the night and attack people.<br><br>
I still trip out when I remember it. I feel rotten right now just thinking about it, and I want to lash out, but it is better said out loud than kept inside and corrode my psyche, whatever is left of it. I still haven't really gotten over it. I don't think I ever will. Try looking for a job with that for a self esteem destroyer.<br><br>
Art  
